---
import { Icon } from 'astro-icon/components';

import Card from '../../layouts/Card.astro';
import InfoColumn from '../../components/InfoColumn.astro';
---
<Card title="Training" metaDescription="I offer various types of training to improve your understanding of accessibility and inclusive design." pageType="service"
  fiUrl="/fi/palvelut/koulutukset/" enUrl="/services/training/" language="en"
>
  <section class="text-center space-y-4">
    <h1>Training</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 max-w-2xl mx-auto text-left">Each training can be fully tailored to your needs. Both the duration and the content can be changed to best suit you. Pricing depends on the type of training, topics and the duration.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 max-w-2xl mx-auto text-left">By default the training is remote, but if you need on-site sessions, let me know!</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 max-w-2xl mx-auto text-left">The training can be organized in Finnish or English.</p>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="services-title">
    <span id="services-title" class="sr-only">The trainings I offer</span>
    <div class="grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4">
      <article class="rounded-2xl shadow-lg p-6 border border-white/50 bg-white/ 95 dark:bg-black/40 dark:border-black/20 flex flex-col justify-between">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dk-purple-header dark:text-lt-perfume flex items-center">For any role</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Example topics and time suggestions:</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 list-disc list-outside pl-3">
              <li class="mb-1"><strong>WCAG in a nutshell</strong> – what the guidelines are about? (30 minutes)</li>
              <li class="mb-1"><strong>More accessible tables</strong> – how to improve usability of tables (30 minutes)</li>
              <li class="mb-1"><strong>Inclusive language</strong> – ensure you don't leave anyone out (30 minutes)</li>
              <li class="mb-1"><strong>Accessibility statement</strong> – what the statement is and how should it be maintained? (30 minutes)</li>
              <li class="mb-1"><strong>Basics of accessibility testing</strong> – how to test accessibility? (1 hour)</li>
              <li class="mb-1"><strong>Screen readers in accessibility testing</strong> – what are screen readers and how can they be used in testing? (1 hour)</li>
            </ul>
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="rounded-2xl shadow-lg p-6 border border-white/50 bg-white/95 dark:bg-black/40 dark:border-black/20 flex flex-col justify-between">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dk-purple-header dark:text-lt-perfume flex items-center">For content editors</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Example topics and time suggestions:</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 list-disc list-outside pl-3">
              <li class="mb-1"><strong>Image accessibility</strong> – what to consider with images? (30 minutes)</li>
              <li class="mb-1"><strong>Text content accessibility</strong> – how to improve content accessibility? (30 minutes)</li>
              <li class="mb-1"><strong>Form accessibility</strong> – how to ensure forms are easy to use (30 minutes)</li>
              <li class="mb-1"><strong>Accessible infographics</strong> – presenting charts on websites (30 minutes)</li>
              <li class="mb-1"><strong>Accessible media content</strong> – how to ensure that videos and audio files are accessible to everyone (light 39 minutes / more comprehensive 1 hour)</li>
              <li class="mb-1"><strong>Accessibility in social media</strong> – what to consider? (30 minutes)</li>
              <li class="mb-1"><strong>Basics of cognitive accessibility</strong> – what choices make content easier for everyone to understand (30 minutes)</li>
            </ul>
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="rounded-2xl shadow-lg p-6 border border-white/50 bg-white/95 dark:bg-black/40 dark:border-black/20 flex flex-col justify-between">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dk-purple-header dark:text-lt-perfume flex items-center">For developers</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Example topics and time suggestions:</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 list-disc list-outside pl-3">
              <li class="mb-1"><strong>Enabling accessible images</strong> – How to take images into account in coding work (30 minutes)</li>
              <li class="mb-1"><strong>Form accessibility</strong> – what measures are required to ensure form accessibility? (1 hour)</li>
              <li class="mb-1"><strong>ARIA basics</strong> – What is ARIA and what is it used for? (30 minutes)</li>
              <li class="mb-1"><strong>Avoid the pitfalls of ARIA</strong> – Make sure you improve accessibility rather than impairing it (light 30 minutes / more comprehensive 1 hour)</li>
            </ul>
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="rounded-2xl shadow-lg p-6 border border-white/50 bg-white/95 dark:bg-black/40 dark:border-black/20 flex flex-col justify-between">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dk-purple-header dark:text-lt-perfume flex items-center">For designers</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Example topics and time suggestions:</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 list-disc list-outside pl-3">
              <li class="mb-1"><strong>Accessible color schemes</strong> – how do you ensure accessible colors? (30 minutes)</li>
              <li class="mb-1"><strong>General accessibility challenges in design</strong>– avoid common pitfalls in designing an accessible service (1 hour)</li>
            </ul>
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="me" class="rounded-2xl shadow-lg p-6 border border-white/50 bg-white/95 dark:bg-black/40 dark:border-black/20">
    <h2 id="content" class="font-bold text-xl text-dk-purple-header dark:text-lt-perfume">Benefits of a training</h2>
    <div class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-3 mt-4">
      <InfoColumn icon="user-group"
        description="Everyone benefits from understanding accessibility better."
      />
      <InfoColumn icon="wrench-screwdriver"
        description="Training gives you the confidence in what you are doing and increases your knowledge."
      />
      <div class="flex items-start gap-3 ">
        <Icon name="list-bullet" class="h-6 w-6 shrink-0 text-dk-purple-header dark:text-lt-perfume" aria-hidden="true" />
        <div>
          <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            Improved accessibility knowledge leads to better collaboration and more inclusive digital experiences.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="me" class="rounded-2xl shadow-lg p-6 border border-white/50 bg-white/95 dark:bg-black/40 dark:border-black/20">
    <h2 id="options" class="font-bold text-xl text-dk-purple-header dark:text-lt-perfume">How the training is formed?</h2>
    <div class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-3 mt-4">
      <div class="flex items-start gap-3 ">
        <Icon name="academic-cap" class="h-6 w-6 shrink-0 text-dk-purple-header dark:text-lt-perfume" aria-hidden="true" />
        <div class="flex flex-col justify-between h-full">
          <div class="flex flex-col">
            <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
              Choose the topics that best suit your team and I'll create a tailored training session for you.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mt-6">
              Usually I recommend having a session for each role separately, but if you prefer, a mixed session can be organized as well.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <div class="flex items-start gap-3 ">
        <Icon name="computer-desktop" class="h-6 w-6 shrink-0 text-dk-purple-header dark:text-lt-perfume" aria-hidden="true" />
        <div class="flex flex-col justify-between h-full">
          <div class="flex flex-col">
            <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
              Some topics benefit from practical exercises. For example, screen reader testing can be practiced during the training.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mt-6">
              Let me know if you'd like to include practical exercises in the training based on your website or application.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mt-6">
              NB! For practical exercises, it's best if each participant has their own device to work on.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <div class="flex items-start gap-3 ">
        <Icon name="presentation-chart-line" class="h-6 w-6 shrink-0 text-dk-purple-header dark:text-lt-perfume" aria-hidden="true" />
        <div class="flex flex-col justify-between h-full">
          <div>
            <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
              Let's define the duration together based on your needs. Typical training sessions last between 30 minutes to 2 hours.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mt-6">
              If needed, the training can be divided into multiple sessions to better fit your schedule.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mt-6">
              A training in presentation form requires less time than one that includes practical exercises.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="text-center space-y-4">
    <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Interested in working together?</p>
    <a href="mailto:sanna.kramsi@exove.com" class="inline-block px-6 py-3 rounded-xl bg-dk-purple-header dark:bg-lt-perfume text-white dark:text-black font-medium hover:opacity-90">Contact me</a>
  </section>
</Card>